author: Devon Jefferson
title: Tuki Carter - Commando
text:
0 NOT FEELING IT 0 MAKE IT STOP HNHH PREMIERE! Tuki Carter shares his new single "Commando" from his upcoming album "Flowers And Planes." 
Tuki Carter ended 2016 strong with the release of his Tuki Toker mixtape. Now the Taylor Gang rapper is back to work in 2017 and has shared his new single "Commando" along with the announcement of his upcoming album Flowers And Planes . 
"Commando" is an absolute banger showcasing Tuki's unique and potent flow over slumping production courtesy of Big Jerm. Tuki is feeling like Rambo on this track and it's only right that he does as he tears through this single with a ferocious and powerful tenacity that rivals the iconic action hero. 
Tuki says that Flowers And Planes has something for everyone and will indulge the interests of weed enthusiast just as much as it will entertain art lovers, dreamers and so many more. 
"The concept of Flowers and Planes is a deeply personal but is relatable at the same time. It’s based on weed but you don’t have to be a smoker to relate - anyone who appreciates art, dreams, and aspirations will vibe to it." says Tuki. 
Check out the new single and stay tuned for Tuki Carter's Flowers And Planes album set for release on April 7th.
